direction: right

*.style.border-radius: 8
*.style.font-size: 13
*.style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
*.style.stroke: "#333333"

# --- Entry ---

entry: |md
  **docs-review-content-quality**

  - review changed content
    + context
  - no scripts / no agents
  - checklist-driven
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Checklist container: 6 review dimensions ---

checklist: 6 review dimensions {
  style.fill: "#ececec"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2

  flow: |md
    **Logical flow**

    - logical order
    - prerequisites first
    - lead-in sentences
  |
  journey: |md
    **User journey**

    - clear user goal
    - task-oriented
    - troubleshooting
  |
  organization: |md
    **Organization**

    - group related info
    - workflow structure
    - right pacing
  |
  focus: |md
    **Customer focus**

    - action-oriented
    - "how do I..."
      not "what is..."
  |
  scannability: |md
    **Scannability**

    - lists, tables
    - descriptive headings
    - easy to find
  |
  conciseness: |md
    **Conciseness**

    - cut fluff / obvious
    - remove self-referential
    - trim redundant phrases
  |
}

# --- Classification ---

classify: |md
  **Classify each issue**

  - required = unclear /
    missing content
  - [SUGGESTION] = shorter /
    better organized
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Output ---

report: |md
  **Issues list**

  - required issues
  - [SUGGESTION] issues
  - per-dimension findings
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Flow ---

entry -> checklist
checklist -> classify: "issues found"
classify -> report
